BEING A

No sp. nn. = no specific names

n. b. = not consistently binominal
n. L. = no Linnean names
n. z. = no systematic zoology

Bulletin I was a monthly, II was in 2 parts ; the "imprimatur" gives clue to the dates ; from 1837-41 the volume number was dropped and the parts were expressed in signatures ; in 1842 the volume number was resumed ; number of parts issued in year varied ; in 1837 vol. the 8 parts were each separately paged ; from 1845 the vols. were divided into two as well as into four parts ; imprimatur of XXII (1) 1849 is misdated 1849 for 1848. IV of Fischer de W.'s "Entom. Ross." ; Dr. T. Tolmachev has verified the entries in vol. I for me from a copy in Russia.]
